  "text": "3.5.3. Hidden Markov models. Hidden Markov model (HMM) is a widely used and effective tool for modeling the dependency structure [CITATION_1] ). Suppose we observe a mixture of null and non-null hypotheses and expect that the non-nulls appear in clusters. In an HMM, the sequence of the unknown (hidden) null and non-null states is assumed to form a Markov chain (θi)",
